title: R Notebook
text: phyf package working phylogenetic data implements novel phylogenetic data structure called ‘phylogenetic flow’. structures convenient fast types phylogenetic trait models also make easy manipulate phylogeny along associated data. Let’s start loading packages need today, explore dataset work ! bird_beak_codes pf object. pf object type data.frame includes phylogenetic information special type column. convention column called phlo. Let’s print look: phlo column special R vector called pfc object (phylogenetic flow collection). familiar spatial analysis R, might noticed phyf heavily inspired sf package, uses similar naming conventions. pfc object can extracted usual way: printout gives sense underlying structure phylogenetic flow. Essentially list pathways (‘flows’) root phylogeny tips (internal nodes). makes fair bit redundant information , counter-intuitively part makes efficient. Another way visualizing structure sparse matrix (efficiency really lies). row ‘flow’ root terminal node (internal nodes ‘fake’ terminal nodes). column edge phylogeny (named ’s end node). easy convert pf pfc phylo object ape. also simple make pf pfc phylo object. easy convert pf pfc phylo object ape. also simple make pf pfc phylo object. data interested example ‘latent codes’ estimated previously deep learning model trained PyTorch (using Python). model ported R (using torch package). Let’s look . One can use tidyverse ‘verbs’ pf object. first look like?

text: Even though fibre pretty fast, might want spend time fit model 64 variables ~13,000 edges phylogeny (though take less half hour). , first thing filter dataset clade interest, process learn can easily filter pf subtree. use pf_filter_with_mrca() function. pf_filter_with_mrca() filters pf index phylogenetic pfc. doesn’t just filter index, instead finds recent common ancestor (MRCA) nodes referenced index. filters elements pf represent descendants MRCA. way can just feed set species represent clade, filter return species clade well internal nodes. example returns tips internal nodes Pelecaniformes, indexing just two species whose MRCA root node clade.  can use filter() style syntax function. use "Order" column get just “Tinamiformes”.  Use box filter bird_beak_codes whatever subset species want. probably want least hundred species really show capabilities fibre fibre accepts matrix left hand side formula save type large number variables. smaller numbers traits, use following syntax well: trait_1 + trait_2 + trait_3 ~ bre_brownian(phlo). fibre currently supports formula interface, soon support specifying model passing x y matrices data.frames, also support tidymodels recipe objects. run model Pelecaniformes:
code: ## use spoonbill and pelican Pelecaniformes <- bird_beak_codes %>%   pf_filter_with_mrca(label %in% c("Platalea_leucorodia", "Pelecanus_crispus")) plot(Pelecaniformes) ## use spoonbill and pelican Tinamiformes <- bird_beak_codes %>%   pf_filter_with_mrca(Order == "TINAMIFORMES") plot(Tinamiformes) codes <- Pelecaniformes %>%   select(starts_with("latent_")) %>%   as.matrix() %>%   scale()  Pelecaniformes$codes <- codes fit <- fibre(codes ~ bre_brownian(phlo, standardise = FALSE), data = Pelecaniformes, engine = "glmnet",              family = "mgaussian", engine_options = title: Make to the root-to-tip matrix of a phylogeny — make_root2tip
text: phy object class phylo containing phylogeny generate root--tip matrix . Must rooted phylogeny can contain polytomies (.binary(phy) can FALSE). return_nodes nodes return rows ? (Can "tips", "internal" ""). return_type return_nodes == "", pass "matrix" return matrix node types bound together using rbind, pass "list" return two separate matrices list ("tips" first element "internal" second). Ignored return_nodes != "". return_ages vector node 'ages' added attribute named "ages" return value? 'ages' defined total distance node phylogenies root. Note really age phylogeny time tree opposite usual meaning age, , measure age clade descending node, much time (change accumulated) since common ancestor whole phylogeny (root) node reached. definition 'age' makes sense whether phylogeny time-tree . time-tree usual definition age can calculated subtracted focal node's age age tips (time-tree). order Can "first_order" "second_order", specifying whether return root--tip matrix first order second order specification. See documentation fibre() description difference. sparse returned root--tip matrix use sparse matrix representation? FALSE regular dense matrix returned. sparse matrix representation recommended, especially large trees. Beyond certain size tree, sparse return work, dense matrix exhaust memory. root--tip matrices quite sparse, can represent large trees dense matrices (sparse exactly depends shape tree). return_parent TRUE, parent node, matching root tip matrix columns, returned attribute "parents".

title: Tidy eval helpers — tidyeval
text: page lists tidy eval tools reexported package rlang. learn using tidy eval scripts packages high level, see dplyr programming vignette ggplot2 packages vignette. Metaprogramming section Advanced R may also useful deeper dive. tidy eval operators {{, !!, !!! syntactic constructs specially interpreted tidy eval functions. mostly need {{, !! !!! advanced operators use simple cases. curly-curly operator {{ allows tunnel data-variables passed function arguments inside tidy eval functions. {{ designed individual arguments. pass multiple arguments contained dots, use ... normal way.   enquo() enquos() delay execution one several function arguments. former returns single expression, latter returns list expressions. defused, expressions longer evaluate . must injected back evaluation context !! (single expression) !!! (list expressions).   simple case, code equivalent usage {{ ... . Defusing enquo() enquos() needed complex cases, instance need inspect modify expressions way. .data pronoun object represents current slice data. variable name string, use .data pronoun subset variable [[.   Another tidy eval operator :=. makes possible use glue curly-curly syntax LHS =. technical reasons, R language support complex expressions left =, use := workaround.   Many tidy eval functions like dplyr::mutate() dplyr::summarise() give automatic name unnamed inputs. need create sort automatic names , use as_label(). instance, glue-tunnelling syntax can reproduced manually :   Expressions defused enquo() (tunnelled {{) need simple column names, can arbitrarily complex. as_label() handles cases gracefully. code assumes simple column name, use as_name() instead. safer throws error input name expected.
code: my_function <- function(data, var, ...) {   data %>%     group_by(...) %>%     summarise(mean = mean({{ var }})) } my_function <- function(data, var, ...) {   # Defuse   var <- enquo(var)   dots <- enquos(...)    # Inject   data %>%     group_by(!!!dots) %>%     summarise(mean = mean(!!var)) } my_var <- "disp" mtcars %>% summarise(mean = mean(.data[[my_var]])) my_function <- function(data, var, suffix = "foo") {   # Use `{{` to tunnel function arguments and the usual glue   # operator `{` to interpolate plain strings.   data %>%     summarise("{{ var }}_mean_{suffix}" := mean({{ var }})) } my_function <- function(data, var, suffix = "foo") {   var <- enquo(var)   prefix <- as_label(var)   data %>%     summarise("{prefix}_mean_{suffix}" := mean(!!var)) }
